A 30 year old woman has been sentenced to life imprisonment for the rape of a ten year old boy at Eshowe in northern KwaZulu-Natal. Police spokesperson Thulani Zwane says the suspect was found guilty, after the court heard details of how she raped the boy at his home.” “The incident was reported last year in February at Eshowe area when there was a party in the victims homestead and during the night when they were sleeping in the rondoval it is alleged that the suspect allegedly raped this 10 year old while they were inside the house and someone heard the noise as a result reported to the family. The family members then went to the police station to report the rape case. The boy also admitted that it’s not the first time that he was raped by this suspect. Therefore the suspect was then arrested by the family violence child protection sexual offences unit and she was charged accordingly.”